00:03:00.300 --> 00:03:03.740
It's a particular pleasure to be
with all of you this afternoon

00:03:03.740 --> 00:03:07.430
because I'm not on a book tour.

00:03:07.430 --> 00:03:09.050
Make no mistake.

00:03:09.050 --> 00:03:10.380
I like book tours.

00:03:10.380 --> 00:03:13.100
It wasn't all that long ago
that my book sold briskly

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:15.980
but only among people
with my last name.

00:03:15.980 --> 00:03:18.870
I try never to lose sight of that.

00:03:18.870 --> 00:03:20.430
Most people presume, however,

00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:22.730
that book tours are
unbelievably glamorous.

00:03:22.730 --> 00:03:25.630
You jet around the country and
you hang with Oprah and Katie

00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:28.700
and Terry Gross and sell
whole pallets of books.

00:03:28.700 --> 00:03:31.360
But, the reality of
most book tours is this.

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:34.900
They have moments that
are far more humbling

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:38.470
than our honorific this afternoon.

00:03:38.470 --> 00:03:40.030
I will share with you but one.

00:03:40.030 --> 00:03:42.910
I am in Memphis, Tennessee.

00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:45.850
I get to the airport at five
in the morning because I am

00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:49.370
on a 6 a.m. flight to
Jackson, Mississippi.

00:03:49.370 --> 00:03:53.610
When I get there everything on
the concourse is closed except

00:03:53.610 --> 00:03:58.260
for one guy with a cart selling
something he calls a gritty cat.

00:03:58.260 --> 00:04:01.490
A bear claw pastry that has
been deep fried in grits.

00:04:01.490 --> 00:04:05.270
I'm thinking to myself I'm going
to have one of those bad boys.

00:04:05.270 --> 00:04:07.620
I'm just about to get on
a turbo prop, why not.

00:04:07.620 --> 00:04:10.260
So, I had my gritty cat.

00:04:10.260 --> 00:04:11.560
It's not bad.

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:12.860
Get on the plane.

00:04:12.860 --> 00:04:15.410
It's a 17-seater and there
are three other passengers,

00:04:15.410 --> 00:04:17.540
and it's a really choppy rainy day.

00:04:17.540 --> 00:04:21.500 position:56%
And, so, the pilot says we're going
to be on the tarmac for a little bit

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:24.900
and it's going to be a choppy
ride, no cabin service.

00:04:24.900 --> 00:04:28.010
We take off and it is choppy.

00:04:28.010 --> 00:04:30.220
We've been in the air no
more than, I don't know,

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:34.040
three and a half minutes when the
woman two rows behind me vomits.

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:38.640
So, I'm thinking to myself
I'm a frequent flier but just

00:04:38.640 --> 00:04:40.300
in case let's get the
air sickness bag.

00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:42.900
So, I reach into in seat pocket
to get the air sickness bag

00:04:42.900 --> 00:04:44.790
and there's not one there.

00:04:44.790 --> 00:04:48.310
At which point the gentleman
a few rows ahead of me vomits.

00:04:48.310 --> 00:04:52.280
So, I'm thinking to myself
these are more desperate times

00:04:52.280 --> 00:04:53.580
than you realize.

00:04:53.580 --> 00:04:58.800
So, I unbuckle, stand up
planning to go seat to seat

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:00.100
to find an air sickness bag.

00:05:00.100 --> 00:05:01.400
So, I stand up unbuckled

00:05:01.400 --> 00:05:04.390
and the flight attendant
says to me sir, sit down.

00:05:04.390 --> 00:05:05.690
Sit down now.

00:05:05.690 --> 00:05:08.860
And, in a post 911 era when a
flight attendant says sit down,

00:05:08.860 --> 00:05:10.630
sit down now, you do, and I did.

00:05:10.630 --> 00:05:14.370
And, at that point, the third other
passenger vomited leaving me the

00:05:14.370 --> 00:05:17.140
last passenger standing.

00:05:17.140 --> 00:05:22.280
So, we do level out, and we are
circling for a really long time

00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:25.940
over Jackson because
the air is so choppy,

00:05:25.940 --> 00:05:29.240
and I'm concreasingly
worried about this chop

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:30.540
and whether I'm going to make it.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.230
But, finally, the pilot says
we're about to begin our descent.

00:05:33.230 --> 00:05:38.030 position:56%
And I'm thinking you're good, but we
hit a bump, and it was pretty scary.

00:05:38.030 --> 00:05:40.040
So, I reach into the
seat pocket ahead of me,

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:44.340
take out the in flight magazine,
rip out two thick glossy pages,

00:05:44.340 --> 00:05:47.440
swirl them into a snow
cone, fold the bottom.

00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:50.390
And, I don't know whether it is
a thousand feet above Jackson

00:05:50.390 --> 00:05:53.400
or 2,000 feet above Jackson,
but you're looking at the guy

00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:58.230
who created the first ever
airborne snow cone of vomit.

00:05:58.230 --> 00:05:59.640
So, we land.

00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:01.140
And, the flight attendants
very grateful

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:03.870
that I don't give him my
airborne snow cone of vomit.

00:06:03.870 --> 00:06:05.170
I go to the men's room.

00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:07.170
I clean myself up.

00:06:07.170 --> 00:06:09.030
And, then I go to baggage.

00:06:09.030 --> 00:06:13.610
Whenever you are on a book tour
your publisher gives you an escort.

00:06:13.610 --> 00:06:14.910
Not that kind.

00:06:14.910 --> 00:06:18.820
These are the lovely woman and men
who know where all of the libraries

00:06:18.820 --> 00:06:21.740
and the book stores are and they
get you to and from the airport

00:06:21.740 --> 00:06:27.000 position:56%
and you find them in baggage because
they are holding up your book.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:30.620
So, I go into baggage and I
see a woman holding a book.

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:34.200
Not my book, and I'm thinking
wow, that's a cookbook.

00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:37.590
One of the people on the
plane with you was a chef.

00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:39.990
But, then she says Chris.

00:06:39.990 --> 00:06:41.600
And, I said yes.

00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:44.110
And, she says hi -- and
she introduces herself --

00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:47.360
and she says I forgot your book
at home but I found this cookbook

00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:51.820
in the back seat of the car and
figured it would do just fine.

00:06:51.820 --> 00:06:54.590
And then she says I
got some bad news.

00:06:54.590 --> 00:06:57.780
You circled so long that
you missed your slot

00:06:57.780 --> 00:07:00.250
on the public radio station.

00:07:00.250 --> 00:07:01.550
And, I said that's okay.

00:07:01.550 --> 00:07:04.100
And, then she says
you must be hungry.

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:05.910
And, as a matter of fact, I was.

00:07:05.910 --> 00:07:11.100
And, so she said I'm going to bring
you to the best waffles in Jackson.

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:12.400
And, I get in the car with her.

00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:14.360
And, we drive and we
drive, and all of a sudden,

00:07:14.360 --> 00:07:16.790
