me into her home

00:09:12.990 --> 00:09:15.660
and her family it was
a great, great day.

00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:21.960 position:56%
It's a particular pleasure to be at
this book festival because it is all

00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:27.660
about libraries and the
Library of Congress.

00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:30.900
I am a novelist for lot of reasons.

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:33.650
But, a big one are libraries.

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:40.000
And, very specifically the
Hialeah Miami Lakes public library

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.220
in south Florida.

00:09:42.220 --> 00:09:46.990
When I was in eighth grade,
my family moved from a suburb

00:09:46.990 --> 00:09:48.920
of New York City to Miami, Florida,

00:09:48.920 --> 00:09:52.120
which is arguably another
suburb of New York City.

00:09:53.160 --> 00:09:56.070
And, we moved there the
Friday of Labor Day weekend.

00:09:56.070 --> 00:09:59.930
That Tuesday, I started school
at Palm Springs Junior High.

00:09:59.930 --> 00:10:02.960
And, then I went to see
my new orthodontist.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:06.480
A sagest it would turn
out if there ever was one.

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:09.740
He gave me some orthodontic
headgear that looked

00:10:09.740 --> 00:10:13.270
like the business end of a back ho.

00:10:13.270 --> 00:10:16.490
Think Bane from the movie
Batman, the Dark Knight.

00:10:16.490 --> 00:10:19.520
And, I had to wear this
device for four hours a day.

00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:21.370
I wasn't allowed to sleep
when I was wearing it,

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:22.670
I couldn't speak when
I was wearing it.

00:10:22.670 --> 00:10:26.230
So, I would come home from
Palm Springs Junior High.

00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:29.240
I would put in my headgear
and I would go

00:10:29.240 --> 00:10:34.700
to the Hialeah Miami Lakes
public library and I would read.

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:37.890
And, I would read so
many of the books

00:10:37.890 --> 00:10:43.000
that an eighth grader was likely
to read in the late 1970's.

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:48.100
Steven King had started publishing
his remarkable grand [inaudible].

00:10:48.100 --> 00:10:52.980
I read William Peter
Blatty's, The Exorcist.

00:10:52.980 --> 00:10:57.370
Peter Benchley's deceptively
wonderful and really appropriate

00:10:57.370 --> 00:11:00.490
